This file is the project's living priority queue — a markdown table of open engineering tasks ranked by impact then difficulty, read by contributors deciding what to work on next.

It's a flat data file, not code: one Markdown table with columns `task | description | impact | difficulty`, sorted high-impact/easy-difficulty first within each impact band. The header points to `ctx-context .` as the source of truth for derived architecture and `docs/DECISIONS.md` for rationale — this file itself carries no rationale, only action items.

Non-obvious behavior: several rows reference specific line numbers and behaviors in other files as of when they were written (e.g. "checks.rs:103,113", "`is_secret` compares the basename case-sensitively") — these can drift out of sync with the actual code since nothing re-validates the table against source. Treat row contents as claims to verify, not guaranteed-current facts.

Editing this file means adding/removing/reprioritizing rows — no schema enforcement, so keep column order and sort convention (impact desc, then difficulty asc within impact) consistent when inserting new tasks.